<p><strong>nc</strong>(tcp client/server for everything related to tcp or udp: sending, receiving. Alternative to telnet)</p>

<ul>
  <li>scan if a port is open on a remote system. <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">nc -vz localhost 9000</code></li>
  <li>oull the banner information (helpful information about operating system and services versions) from a remote system;</li>
  <li>connect to a network service manually with listening</li>
  <li>remote administration for transferring of files: â€œpipeâ€ into TCP for batch data transfer, because it will not alter any byte sent through it. If you need something likeÂ catÂ but for TCP, useÂ nc</li>
</ul>

